{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "During the training stage, the model is trained on N-way-K-shot tasks or episodes sampled from the training set D train.Each N-way-K-shot task or episode includes a support set and a query set.",
    "To create an N-way-K-shot task, we randomly sample N event types from Y train.",
    "Then, for each of the N event types, we randomly select K instances as the support set S = {X i, a i, Y i } N ×K i=1 and M instances as the query set Q = {X i, a i, Y i } N ×M i=1, and S ∩ Q = ∅.",
    "The support set is similar to the training set in traditional supervised learning but contains only a few samples.",
    "The query set acts as the test set but is used to compute gradients for updating model parameters [14]."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The query set acts as the test set but is used to compute gradients for updating model parameters [14]."
  ]
}